authors.name: Andrea R Daniel
authors.note: This protocol was adapted from Sean McCucheon's work in the Gersbach lab at Duke University.

description: {"blocks":[{"key":"2ln9a","text":"This is a protocol describes methods for performing RNAseq using human CD8+ T cells overexpressing BATF3 or a GFP control.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
manuscript_citation: {"blocks":[{"key":"1f12k","text":"McCutcheon, S.R., Swartz, A.M., Brown, M.C. et al. Transcriptional and epigenetic regulators of human CD8+ T cell function identified through orthogonal CRISPR screens.Nat Genet (2023). https://doi.org/10.1038/s41588-023-01554-0","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":44,"length":6},{"style":"italic","offset":168,"length":9},{"style":"sup","offset":105,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"fh1uq","text":"Plate 1.2 x 106 or 7 x 106 HEK293T cells in a 6 well plate or 10 cm dish in the afternoon with 2 mL or 12 mL of complete opti-MEM (Opti-MEM‱ I Reduced Serum Medium supplemented with 1x  Glutamax, 5% FBS, 1 mM Sodium Pyruvate, and 1x MEM Non-Essential Amino Acids).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":139,"length":1}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"emoji","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"20B639908EFB11EEB5700A58A9FEAC02","name":":tm:"}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bbv1g","text":"The next morning, transfect HEK293T cells with 0.5 μg pMD2.G, 1.5 μg psPAX2, and 0.5 μg transgene for 6 well plates or 3.25 μg pMD2.G, 9.75 μg psPAX2, and 4.3 μg transgene for 10 cm dishes using Lipofectamine 3000.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4fjp7","text":"Exchanged media 6 hours after transfection and collect and pool lentiviral supernatant at 24 hours and 48 hours after transfection.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Transduction of primary human CD8+ T cells
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"8skac","text":"Centrifuged lentiviral supernatant at 600g for 10 min to remove cellular debris. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":41,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Transduction of primary human CD8+ T cells
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"fifcb","text":"Concentrate lentivirus to 50–100× the initial concentration using Lenti-X Concentrator (Takara Bio). ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Transduction of primary human CD8+ T cells
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"75hui","text":"Transduce T cells at 5–10% v/v of concentrated lentivirus at 24 h post-activation. For dual transduction experiments, T cells were serially transduced at 24 h and 48 h.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7s5ds","text":"Isolated CD8+ T cells from individual donors were obtianed directly from vials purchased from StemCell Technologies. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":12,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9n498","text":"Culture T cells were in PRIME-XV T cell Expansion XSFM (FujiFilm) supplemented with 5% human platelet lysate (Compass Biomed), 100 U ml−1 penicillin and 100 μg ml−1 streptomycin. All media were supplemented with 100 U ml−1 human IL-2 (Peprotech). ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":135,"length":2},{"style":"sup","offset":162,"length":2},{"style":"sup","offset":220,"length":2}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6049q","text":"T cells overexpressing either BATF3 or GFP were cultured for 10 days post transduction.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1fhnn","text":"RNA was isolated using Norgen’s Total RNA Purification Plus Kit and submitted to Azenta (formerly Genewiz) for standard RNA-seq with polyA selection.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"77mu7","text":"Reads were first trimmed using Trimmomatic72 v0.32 to remove adapters and then aligned to GRCh38 using STAR v2.4.1a aligner.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":42,"length":2}],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":42,"length":2}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"A4B63B5C8EFD11EEB5700A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41588-023-01554-0#ref-CR72"}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ajr5j","text":"Gene counts were obtained with featureCounts73 from the subread package (version 1.4.6-p4) using the comprehensive gene annotation in Gencode v22.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":44,"length":2}],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":44,"length":2}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"BB3ACEB68EFD11EEB5700A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41588-023-01554-0#ref-CR73"}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"c78v4","text":"Differential expression analysis was determined with DESeq2 (ref. 68) where gene counts are fitted into a negative binomial generalized linear model and a Wald test determines significant DEGs. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":66,"length":2}],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":66,"length":2}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"C5E352FD8EFD11EEB5700A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41588-023-01554-0#ref-CR68"}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4484g","text":"DESeq2 results of RNA-seq analyses with BATF3 OE and ZNF217 or GATA3 KO are presented in Supplementary Tables 4 and 7, respectively. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":110,"length":1},{"key":1,"offset":116,"length":1}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"DC48E6718EFD11EEB5700A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41588-023-01554-0#MOESM3"}},"1":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"DC48E6718EFD11EEB5700A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41588-023-01554-0#MOESM3"}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9lu2o","text":"Upregulated and downregulated DEGs were input into EnrichR’s GO Biological Processes 2021 database71 for functional annotation.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sup","offset":98,"length":2}],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":98,"length":2}],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"link","mutability":"MUTABLE","data":{"guid":"E156D4F48EFD11EEB5700A58A9FEAC02","url":"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41588-023-01554-0#ref-CR71"}}}}
